Check on status of data requests

Source: R/requests.R
nc_requests.Rd

List pending or completed data requests for a given user.

nc_requests(request_id = NULL, username)

Arguments

request_id

Numeric. Specific request id to check or download.
username

Character vector. Username for http://naturecounts.ca. If provided, the user will be prompted for a password. If left NULL, only public collections will be returned.

Value

data frame

request_id's

There are two types of data requests: ones made through the api (i.e. this naturecounts R package) and those made through the online Web Request Form. Each request generates a request id which identifies the filter set and collections requested.

Requests made through this package via the nc_data_dl() function only return data the user has access to. If data was successfully downloaded, the user can see the request details with the nc_requests() function.

Requests made through the online Web Request Form may include collections to which the user does not have access. nc_requests() will list the requests along with the approval status (either 'approved' or 'pending').

Any approved request id can be downloaded by supplying the request_id to nc_data_dl() (e.g., nc_data_dl(request_id = 152000, username = "USER")).

Examples

nc_requests(username = "sample")
